  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering penalties can include significant fines and prison time. Specific penalties depend on the details of the offense, but generally involve:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n\n2. Financial Penalties:\n- Fines can be up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved in the transaction\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe exact sentence depends on factors like the amount of money involved, number of transactions, and specific circumstances of the offense. Consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate and current information about specific cases.",
